    <a title="Roshio" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1974093-roshio"><img alt="Roshio" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1315651929p2/1974093.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/127395628?book_show_action=true">Oct 22, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Roshio" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Roshio" href="/user/show/1974093-roshio">Roshio</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1974093-roshio?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1974093-roshio?shelf=dark-fantasy">dark-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer127395628" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2210692446978813102">Expectations. Expectations have a way of ruining a book for me. I build up a book and if it doesn&apos;t meet the standards I have already set, it disappoints me a lot more than if I&apos;d known nothing about it. Unfortunately this is what happened with this book. For me this is mostly a story of star crossed lovers who happen to have their love set in a fantasy world. So its &apos;fantasy romance&apos; so to speak. Fortunately I like star crossed lovers so I liked this book but what I wanted was dark fantasy, gri</span>
  <span id="freeText2210692446978813102" style="display:none">Expectations. Expectations have a way of ruining a book for me. I build up a book and if it doesn't meet the standards I have already set, it disappoints me a lot more than if I'd known nothing about it. Unfortunately this is what happened with this book. For me this is mostly a story of star crossed lovers who happen to have their love set in a fantasy world. So its 'fantasy romance' so to speak. Fortunately I like star crossed lovers so I liked this book but what I wanted was dark fantasy, grim, cruel, harsh. I didn't really get that from this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2210692446978813102" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
